-005529 [P&P] LOT 1936  (corresponding photographic print)", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["summit county", "united states", "safety film negatives", "akron", "ohio"], "timestamp": "2022-04-25T15:24:37.473Z", "title": "Salvage. Scrap rubber collection. Have you any old rubber lying around? Look at this picture closely and you will find many things that you too can contribute to the national scrap rubber pile. This accumulation in the yards of the Dowenthal Company in Akron, Ohio, contains old bicycle tires, hot water bottles, fruit jar rings, rubber heals and soles, floor mats, tire patches, hose connections, tubing, gaskets, fan belts, washers, in fact, everything but rubber checks", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017693199/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/fsa/item/2017699410/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017699410/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2017699410/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/fsa.8b01089", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/fsa.8b01089/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2017699410"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["united states. office of war information", "palmer, alfred t."], "date": "1941-01-01", "dates": ["1941"], "description": ["1 negative : safety ; 4 x 5 inches or smaller."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-09-01T20:10:54.612Z", "group": ["fsa", "catalog-split-07", "catalog", "fsa-owi-black-and-white-negatives", "main-catalog-split-07", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017699410/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b01000/8b01000/8b01089_150px.jpg#h=118&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b01000/8b01000/8b01089t.gif#h=118&w=150", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b01000/8b01000/8b01089r.jpg#h=503&w=640", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b01000/8b01000/8b01089v.jpg#h=805&w=1024"], "index": 6, "language": ["english"], "location": ["summit county", "united states", "ohio", "akron"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/19645204", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017699410", "2017699410", "http://www.loc.gov/item/oem2002010340/pp", "2017-05-15t14:24:28"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["prints and photographs division", "catalog", "lot 2060", "american memory", "prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "farm security administration/office of war information black-and-white negatives"], "score": 32.008778, "shelf_id": "LC-USE6- D-001665 [P&P] LOT 2060  (corresponding photographic print)", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["summit county", "united states", "safety film negatives", "akron", "ohio"], "timestamp": "2022-04-25T15:41:37.634Z", "title": "Loading raw rubber. Bales of raw rubber, removed from wooden crates in which they have traveled from Singapore, are wheeled up to this endless chain loader, which will automatically feed it into the \"guillotine,\" the first step in making tires at an Ohio tire plant", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017699410/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/fsa/item/2017690675/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017690675/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2017690675/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/fsa.8b02052", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/fsa.8b02052/", "http://lccn.loc.gov/2017690675"], "campaigns": [], "contributor": ["united states. office of war information", "palmer, alfred t."], "date": "1942-01-01", "dates": ["1942"], "description": ["1 negative : safety ; 4 x 5 inches or smaller."], "digitized": true, "extract_timestamp": "2021-09-01T20:10:10.699Z", "group": ["fsa", "catalog-split-11", "catalog", "fsa-owi-black-and-white-negatives", "main-catalog-split-11", "main-catalog"], "hassegments": false, "id": "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017690675/", "image_url": ["https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b02000/8b02000/8b02052_150px.jpg#h=150&w=118", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b02000/8b02000/8b02052t.gif#h=150&w=118", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b02000/8b02000/8b02052r.jpg#h=640&w=503", "https://tile.loc.gov/storage-services/service/pnp/fsa/8b02000/8b02000/8b02052v.jpg#h=1024&w=805"], "index": 7, "language": ["english"], "location": ["summit county", "united states", "ohio", "akron"], "mime_type": ["image/gif", "image/jpg", "image/tif"], "number": ["http://www.loc.gov/item/2017690675", "http://www.loc.gov/item/19635779", "2017690675", "2017-05-15t08:24:42", "http://www.loc.gov/item/oem2002001602/pp"], "online_format": ["image"], "original_format": ["photo, print, drawing"], "partof": ["prints and photographs division", "catalog", "lot 2063", "american memory", "prints & photographs online catalog (library of congress)", "farm security administration/office of war information black-and-white negatives"], "score": 32.008778, "shelf_id": "LC-USE6- D-002805 [P&P] LOT 2063  (corresponding photographic print)", "site": ["pictures", "catalog"], "subject": ["summit county", "united states", "safety film negatives", "akron", "ohio"], "timestamp": "2022-04-25T15:18:13.353Z", "title": "Giant tire manufacturer. This husky workman, standing six feet four inches tall, looks small indeed as he uses air pressure to clean the lid of the world's largest vulcanizing unit in an Eastern tire plant. The top section of this mold being prepared to vulcanize a large bullet-sealing gasoline tank, weighs sixteen tons and can also be used to vulcanize tires over ten feet in diameter", "url": "https://www.loc.gov/item/2017690675/"}, {"access_restricted": false, "aka": ["http://www.loc.gov/pictures/collection/fsa/item/2017690676/", "http://www.loc.gov/item/2017690676/", "http://www.loc.gov/pictures/item/2017690676/", "https://hdl.loc.gov/loc.pnp/fsa.8b02053", "http://www.loc.gov/resource/fsa.8b02053/", "http://lccn.lo